**Explanation:**
- P(A=T) = 0.4 + 0.4 = 0.8, so we sample `a` with `flip(0.8)`
- P(B=T|A=T) = 0.4/0.8 = 0.5, and P(B=T|A=F) = 0.06/0.2 = 0.3
- We sample `b` with a conditional flip: `flip(0.5)` if a is true, else `flip(0.3)`
- This recovers the joint distribution: P(T,T)=0.8×0.5=0.4, P(T,F)=0.8×0.5=0.4, P(F,T)=0.2×0.3=0.06, P(F,F)=0.2×0.7=0.14 ✓

